uo;ll eventually get their comeuppance at the hands of the PCs in Part Three</p>\n<h3>Ambrose \"Fishguts\" Kroop</h3>\n<p>Ambrose Kroop is the ship&rsquo;s cook, nicknamed &ldquo;Fishguts&rdquo; by the crew, though whether this refers to the contents of his soups or the stains on his apron is unclear. His job is to bring the ship&rsquo;s biscuit on deck at dawn for the crew, and prepare and serve the evening meal. Kroop is a drunkard, but not constantly inebriated, and is a potential ally for the PCs. His unpredictability makes him a frustrating but ultimately useful friend. Like his friend Cut-Throat Grok, Kroop is from the school of hard knocks, but where Grok has become tough, Kroop has capitulated in the face of endless discipline and violence. However, as the adventure progresses and he becomes closer to the PCs, he becomes an increasingly useful ally.</p>\n<p>While Kroop is indifferent to the PCs at the beginning of the adventure, he is, at heart, a friendly salt, and soon becomes attached to any character who makes a modicum of effort as the cook&rsquo;s mate. In general, Kroop likes to cook and drink rum. He is usually insensibly drunk in his quarters during the evening, rarely venturing onto deck after serving the evening meal. Kroop&rsquo;s cook&rsquo;s mate gains a +2 bonus on all checks to inf luence the quartermaster Cut-Throat Grok. Kroop is also happy to lend his mate any equipment from the galley, though stealing it without his permission is easy enough.</p>\n<h3>Cut-Throat Grok</h3>\n<p>Cut-Throat Grok is the <em>Wormwood&rsquo;s </em>quartermaster, a no-nonsense character with a huge scar across her neck. Growing up among pirates is tough for anyone unusual, and Grok got her scar fighting a gang of cutthroats in the alleys of Port Peril who robbed her and left her for dead when she was only 11 years old. Grok is a reedy half-orc who favors dark clothing. She carries a notched greataxe and an array of throwing axes hangs from her belt. Grok frequently grins toothily, and uses appalling curse words, particularly when drunk. Grok is renowned for being tough, and she doesn&rsquo;t suffer fools, but she is a close friend of Ambrose Kroop, whom she sees as someone who&rsquo;s had even worse luck than she&rsquo;s had.</p>\n<p>Grok is usually found in the quartermaster&rsquo;s store (area A9) during the day. In the evenings, she locks the store and carouses on deck, drinking and gambling with the other pirates before returning to her cabin (area A7) to sleep it off.</p>\n<p>Grok loves unusual drink and fine songs, and a character who provides her with at least 20 gp worth of alcohol that isn&rsquo;t rum or who makes a successful DC 15 Perform (song) check gains a +4 bonus on all checks made to inf luence her. If Grok is made friendly, she allows the PCs into the quartermaster&rsquo;s store after normal hours, where PCs can negotiate for equipment with her with additional Diplomacy checks. Recovering a PC&rsquo;s starting equipment is considered simple aid (DC +0), a loan of goods worth up to 150 gp is considered lengthy aid (DC +5), and a loan of 300 gp worth of equipment is considered dangerous aid that could result in punishment, since she might get keelhauled herself for theft (DC +15).</p>\n<h3>Other Officers</h3>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">In addition to the major NPCs detailed on these pages, a number of other officers serve aboard the </span><span class=\"fontstyle2\">Wormwood</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\">.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Although most of these characters play little or no role in this adventure and cannot be inf luenced, the PCs may spot them aboard the ship or hear about them from their fellow pirates. Be aware that some of these NPCs do reappear later in the Skull &amp; Shackles Adventure Path, so you should try to avoid forming any strong relationships between these characters and the PCs at this point.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>","_id":"Tn3ayuWfdb7zWDeg"}
{"name":"Ship Roles","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_2fzh7f9etq5","path":"Seas of Eberron#/CF_SEP/The Wormwood","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Ship Roles</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>All crew members on any ship have specific roles and responsibilities, often with harsh punishments being meted out upon those who shirk their duties. Listed here are some of the standard roles aboard a typical ship. Not all of these roles might be represented on every vessel, but such details can help players understand their characters&rsquo; daily duties.</p>\n<h3>Artificer/Mage</h3>\n<p>Many ships that ply the waters around Khorvaire have an artificer or mage on board. They can be responsible for the functioning of any magical locomotion of the ship, repairs, general arcane knowledge or any number of other magical needs the ship might have. They are also expected to contribute firepower to any ship to ship conflicts that happen on the vessel.&nbsp;</p>\n<h3>Boatswain</h3>\n<p>The boatswain, or bosun (pronounced &ldquo;bosun&rdquo; either way), is responsible for the upper deck of the vessel and above. This makes the boatswain accountable for all rope, rigging, anchors, and sails. At the start of the day, the boatswain and those under her weigh anchor, raise the sails and report on the general condition of the ship&rsquo;s deck to the captain. As she oversees many of the ship&rsquo;s basic daily labors, the boatswain is often responsible for keeping discipline and dispensing punishment.</p>\n<h3>Cabin Boy/Girl</h3>\n<p>Servant to the captain and other officers, this low-ranking and typically young crew member assists other sailors in their duties and runs various errands across the ship, requiring him or her to gain a measure of understanding of almost all the ship&rsquo;s roles.</p>\n<h3>Captain</h3>\n<p>The ultimate authority on any ship, his word is law to all on board. The captain chooses where to sail, what are fitting punishments for breeches in discipline,&nbsp; and who fills the other stations aboard the vessel, among many other command decisions. Leadership can prove perilous, however, as a captain is, above all, meant to secure success for his ship and crew. Failing to do so increases the threat of mutiny.</p>\n<h3>Carpenter</h3>\n<p>No matter what enchantments or alchemical unguents augment a pirate ship, its heart and bones are still wood. This simple fact makes the carpenter one of the most important positions aboard any vessel. Carpenters are chief ly responsible for maintaining the ship below the deck, finding and plugging leaks, repairing damage, and replacing masts and yards.</p>\n<h3>Cook</h3>\n<p>While the quartermaster normally allocates the rations, the cook and his apprentices make and distribute meals to the crew. Although some better-outfitted vessels employ skilled cooks to attend to the captain and the officers, many cooks are drawn from crew members who have suffered crippling injuries, allowing them to still serve even after such trauma.</p>\n<h3>Healer</h3>\n<p>Many ships have a healer on board to tend to any injuries that happen. Whether this is a House Jorasco healer, Jorasco trained, or some herbalist with slight training in healing, depends on the vessel.</p>\n<h3>Master-at-Arms</h3>\n<p>Concerned with the security of the ship, the fitness of the crew, and the dispensing of justice, the master-at-arms typically is one of the most feared and dreaded of a ship&rsquo;s officers.</p>\n<h3>Master Gunner</h3>\n<p>The master gunner is in charge of all shipboard artillery, ensuring the weapons are kept in good working order and that the crew knows how to use them. She maintains the ballistas, catapults, and so on.</p>\n<h3>Quartermaster</h3>\n<p>The quartermaster oversees the supplies and items stored aboard the ship. She maintains the supplies of food and weaponry, oversees the disbursement of food to the cook, and doles out the rum ration to the crew.</p>\n<h3>Rigger</h3>\n<p>Riggers work the rigging and unfurl the sails. In battle, next to that of a boarding party, the riggers&rsquo; job is one of the most dangerous, as they pull enemy vessels near enough to board.</p>\n<h3>Swab</h3>\n<p>Any sailor who mops the decks. Also used as slang for any low-ranking or unskilled crew member.</p>\n</div>\n</div>","_id":"awi25kwR25zOMXzr"}
{"name":"Ship Board Actions","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_2fzh7f9etq5","path":"Seas of Eberron#/CF_SEP/The Wormwood","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>Ship Board Actions</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<p>In addition to their normal jobs on the ship, the PCs can also utilize their time during the day (and night) to explore the ship, scrounger for gear, interact with their shipmates, or attempt to inf luence NPCs.</p>\n<p>With the PCs potentially scattered across the ship working at their jobs, however, there is a danger that early events in the adventure might focus too much upon the actions of individual characters. Some PCs might have more time on their hands and act accordingly. To avoid this, the PCs&rsquo; activities aboard ship&mdash;carrying out their assigned tasks; exploring the ship; robbing, bullying, or befriending shipmates; working; or playing&mdash;are performed as part of ship actions. These actions ref lect the time required to set up or complete an activity, such as gathering enough crew to play a game, scouting out a room to make sure it&rsquo;s empty, and so on. Remember that even the cook&rsquo;s mate has a job to do during the day, and ship actions are meant to ref lect the available time a PC can carve out from his or her work time without going into too much detail.</p>\n<p>Each PC can normally take two ship actions each day, one during the day and one at night. A PC can also attempt to take up to two additional ship actions during the middle watch in the dead of night (any nighttime ship action marked with an asterisk), but to do so the PC must make a successful Constitution check (DC 10, +4 per extra ship action taken) or be fatigued for the next day.</p>\n<p>A list of possible ship actions is presented on the following page. As always, use your judgment as to when these actions are appropriate.</p>\n<table class=\"table interlude-table\" style=\"width: 66%;\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Ship Board Actions</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"black-row\">\n<td>Daytime Actions</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Work Diligently: </strong>Gain a +1 bonus on any one check for a job's daily task.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Influence: </strong>Make normal checks for a job's daily task and make an attempt to influence a single NPC (skill check based on how it is done).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Sneak: </strong>Make normal checks for a job's daily task. Then make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} check to avoid detection, followed by a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} to briefly explore one area of the ship.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Shop: </strong>Take a &ndash;1 penalty on all checks for a job's daily task and visit the quartermaster's store.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Shirk:</strong> Take a &ndash;1 penalty on all checks for a job's daily task and take time exploring one area of the ship. Make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} check to avoid detection, followed by a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} to briefly explore one area of the ship.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"black-row\">\n<td>Nighttime Actions</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Sleep: </strong>Go to bed early and sleep through the night (automatically recover one level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Gamble:</strong> Play or gamble on a game of chance.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Entertain:</strong> Make one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance} to entertain the crew.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Influence:</strong> Attempt to influence a single NPC. (Skill check based on how influencing is done.)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Sneak:</strong> Take time exploring one area of the ship. Make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} check to avoid detection, followed by a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} to explore one area of the ship.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Steal:&nbsp;</strong>Attempt to steal something from a locked door or footlocker. The character must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} roll to avoid being seen as well as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} check.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>","_id":"hzXGZETL4v2wk79N"}
{"_id":"i8HyBdGehv8PTKhy","name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_2fzh7f9etq5","path":"Seas of Eberron#/CF_SEP/The Wormwood","color":"#008000","name":"Seas of Eberron Rules","children":["FJHhcYei8MYZlo2y","Tn3ayuWfdb7zWDeg","hzXGZETL4v2wk79N","MUsb5tMRBzK0Cpo1","9VlOO3cACSA2vHNI","uhUPupisUqsJ8Bb2","awi25kwR25zOMXzr","pBE4GEkspAo8LRDr","u4YdOrQu6X4eS1Ht","Fo0Hd3YInpT7c50D"],"folderPath":[],"icon":"","fontColor":""}},"content":""}
{"name":"The Wormwood Crew","permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{"references":{}},"cf":{"id":"temp_2fzh7f9etq5","path":"Seas of Eberron#/CF_SEP/The Wormwood","color":"#000000"}},"content":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<div class=\"section-header\">\n<h1>The Wormwood Crew</h1>\n</div>\n<div>\n<h2>Officers</h2>\n<p>This is a complete listing of all the officers aboard the <em>Wormwood. </em>Aside from Mister Dabrak, Master Scourge, Ambrose Kroop, and Grok most of the the officers that serve aboard the Wormwood should not be influenced in the beginning of the adventure. They should play little role and the characters should see them on the periphery on the ship.</p>\n<p><strong>Captain Berrigan \"Black Red\" Redeker</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> captain, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />Ruthless captain of the <em>Wormwood</em>.</p>\n<p><strong>Mister Dabrak</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female orc, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> first mate, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />Black Red's bullying and sadistic first mate. She is second-in-command, and her rule is law on deck. She takes an immediate dislike to the PC's and any friends they make among the crew. She is terrified of the captain, however, and has more things on her mind than the PC's. She&rsquo;s suspicious of everyone on the crew, and while he grows to hate the PCs, he does not sully his hands with fighting them unless they attack him, in which case he fights with relish, calling on his allies for aid in dealing with the &ldquo;mutineers.&rdquo; Dabrak is a figure to be hated</p>\n<p><strong>Master Scourge</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;Male half-orc,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;boatswain and master-at-arms,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;hostile<br />Black</p>\n<p><strong>Ambrose \"Fishguts\" Kroop</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> cook, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral<br />Black</p>\n<p><strong>\"Cut-Throat\" Grok</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female half-orc, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> quartermaster, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral<br />Black</p>\n<p><strong>Grovus Stormbeard</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> artificer, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;hostile<br />Sailing master, storm sorcerer, and old friend of the captains.</p>\n<p><strong>Riaris Krine</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> master gunner, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;hostile<br />Black</p>\n<p><strong>Hakrilli Quarne</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> carpenter, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;hostile<br />Black</p>\n<p><strong>Gragoth</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male orc,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> gunner's mate, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;hostile<br />Bootlicker for Dabrak and Scourge.</p>\n<p><strong>Patch \"Salty\"</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> boatswain's mate, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;hostile<br />Sycophant of Dabrak and Scourge.</p>\n<p><strong>\"Caulky\" Tarroon</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female halfling, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> cabin girl, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile</p>\n<p><strong>Owlbear Hartshorn</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male orc, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> none, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral<br />Simplton and \"pet\" of Mr. Dabrak.</p>\n<h2>Crew</h2>\n<p><strong>Sandara Quinn</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female human, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> swab, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> helpful<br />Black</p>\n<p><strong>Barefoot Shamms Toppin<br /></strong><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;Female dwarf,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;rigger,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;neutral<br />A former fisherwoman from Port Krez who never wears shoes.</p>\n<p><strong>Giffer Tibbs</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;Male dwarf,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;neutral<br />A bedraggled dwarf with one eye.</p>\n<p><strong>Rosie Cusswell</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;Female dwarf,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;neutral<br />Short even for a dwarf, Rosie Cusswell is fierce and has more muscles than most of the crew. She also has a fouler mouth than all the crew put together. Rosie is from Cliffscrape, and like the characters was impressed onto the <em>Wormwood's</em> crew. She has been on the ship for over a week and has already made her mark threatening others who mess with her. She has a healthy hatred of Mr. Dabrak and Scourge. She loves food, drink, and tall tales. Anyone who provides her with any of those gains a +1 bonus to any check to influence her. She is missing her fiddle, and has been unable to convince Grok to give it back to her. Any character that can recover her fiddle for her, will immediately made a firm friend of Rosie.</p>\n<p><strong>Tamroth Scrimshaw<br /></strong><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female orc, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> neutral<br />Young lass that is talented in carving scrimshaw.</p>\n<p><strong>\"Badger\" Stonehurler</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;Male dwarf,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;uncooperative<br />An old dwarf who has his gray hear shaved into strips.</p>\n<p><strong>Conchobhar Turlach Dalian<br /></strong><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;Male gnome,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;rigger,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;uncooperative<br />Conchobhar Shortstone is a handsome, honey-tongued gnome who wears a foppish purple hat, an eye patch, and a white silk shirt, and carries a dandyish cane. His appearance is that of someone pretending to be a pirate, rather than a true buccaneer. Conchobhar is a professional gambler who made the mistake of drinking with the&nbsp;<em>Wormwood&rsquo;s</em>&nbsp;crew one night. He has been on ship less than 24 hours at the start of the adventure. Conchobhar is resigned to his fate but is determined to make the most of it, as he&rsquo;s always yearned for the sea anyway. One thing dominates Conchobhar&rsquo;s thinking&mdash;himself. Conchobhar is also a serial womanizer, and female characters gain a +1 bonus on all checks to influence him. He finds Rosie Cusswell magnificent.</p>\n<p><strong>\"Ratline\" Rattsberger</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> uncooperative<br />A rat-faced dwarf with slightly longer arms and three missing fingers.</p>\n<p><strong>Tilly Tordanthan</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> uncooperative<br />A tough joker that likes her rum.</p>\n<p><strong>Arzag</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male hobgoblin, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;unfriendly<br />A very tall hobgolbin ex-slaver.</p>\n<p><strong>Aretta Tarravan</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;Female half-orc,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;unfriendly<br />A bad tempered harlot whose only signs of orc heritage are big orc ears and on larger incisor.</p>\n<p><strong>Crimson \"Cog\" Cogward</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;Male human,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;unfriendly<br />Crimson Cogward (so called after the color his neck turns when he&rsquo;s angry) is a loner, and prone to incredible rages and dark moods. Cog gets pleasure from little other than combat and is quick to get into fistfights, whether because of a chance remark or simple bad luck. Cog actually volunteered to join the crew of the&nbsp;<em>Wormwood</em>. He has spent his first few days aboard stealing and secreting away goods for barter. Cog loves dark tales. A character that can succeed on telling a dark tale to Cog will gain a +1 bonus on checks to influence Cog. Characters who are fighters and favor muscle over talk, interspursing their talk with grisly details will gain a +1 bonus to influence Cog. However, a failed check is likely to elicit a violent response from the angry sailor.</p>\n<p><strong>Sador Chumlett</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male orc, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;unfriendly<br />A fat, pushy bully with a shaved head.</p>\n<p><strong>Jaundiced Sudak</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Female dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />A humorless, greedy mute.</p>\n<p><strong>Maheem</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male human, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;hostile<br />A big man with a permanent scowl.</p>\n<p><strong>Slippery Syl</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;hostile<br />An unhinged murderer who fled to sea to escape the gallows.</p>\n<p><strong>Tam \"Narwhal\" Tate</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span> rigger, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;hostile<br />An old friend of Master Scourge with a large ugly nose and half an ear.</p>\n<p><strong>Jakes Magpie</strong><br /><span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Stat:</strong></em></span> Male dwarf, <span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Job:</strong></em></span>&nbsp;swab,&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ba372a;\"><em><strong>Intial reaction:</strong></em></span> hostile<br />A thief caught stealing from the quartermaster's store and sentenced to keelhauling on the character's first day.&nbsp;</p>\n</div>\n</div>","img":"","_id":"pBE4GEkspAo8LRDr"}
